                        data-module-name="utility-bar-module-print"></div></div></div></div></div><section id="module-position-NiiE3Ze7RK8" class="storytopbar-bucket story-headline-module"><h1 class="asset-headline" itemprop="headline">John Green spreads news of &#39;Paper Towns&#39; director</h1></section><section id="module-position-NiiE3ZfHOl4" class="storytopbar-bucket story-byline-module"><div class="asset-metabar" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><span itemprop="name" class="asset-metabar-author asset-metabar-item"><img class="asset-metabar-avatar" src="http://www.gannett-cdn.com/-mm-/949f4c87696b279904294510d781cbbeb3561f0d/c=0-0-256-256&amp;r=1024x1024&amp;r=26&amp;c=26x26/local/-/media/Indianapolis/USATODAY/2014/03/02//1393782930000-0fa6ed7e3548f8d4dca569621e838b41.jpeg" height="26" width="26"/> David Lindquist, david.lindquist@indystar.com </span><span class="asset-metabar-time asset-metabar-item nobyline">6:06 p.m. EDT September 4, 2014</span></div></section><div class="asset-double-wide double-wide" role="main" itemprop="articleBody"><div id="module-position-NiiE31Y3doQ" class="story-asset story-leadin-asset"><h2 class="lead-in">Jake Schreier hired to oversee mystery based on Florida teens</h2></div><div id="module-position-NiiE31YDqgU" class="story-asset story-metadata-asset"><div class="article-metadata-wrap"><section id="module-position-NiiE3pyF-V4" class="storymetadata-bucket expandable-photo-module"><aside itemprop="associatedMedia" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" class="single-photo expandable-collapsed"><div class="image-wrap"><img class="expand-img-horiz" itemprop="url" src="http://www.gannett-cdn.com/-mm-/0627567c855c8e5689eaed9a975080cde76928ae/c=0-0-1065-801&amp;r=x404&amp;c=534x401/local/-/media/Indianapolis/Indianapolis/2014/09/04/1409861108000-JAKEPAPERTOWNS.jpg" alt="JAKEPAPERTOWNS" /><span class="toggle"></span><meta itemprop="name" content="JAKEPAPERTOWNS" /></div><p class="image-credit-wrap"><span class="js-caption-wrapper"><span class="cutline js-caption">Jake Schreier will direct the &quot;Paper Towns&quot; film.</span><meta itemprop="copyrightHolder" content="" /><span class="credit">(Photo: Getty Images)</span></span></p></aside></section></div></div><div id="module-position-NiiE31ZdiMU" class="story-asset inline-share-tools-asset"><div class="inline-share-tools asset-inline-share-tools asset-inline-share-tools-top"><span
