fore the May 14 soundtrack event for &quot;The Fault in Our Stars&quot; in Los Angeles." width="80" height="45"></a></li></ul></div></div><div class="feature-btns"><div class="ticker feature-btns-control"></div><div class="autoplay feature-btns-control"><span class="playbtn feature-btns-label">Autoplay</span></div><div class="thumbnails feature-btns-control"><span class="thumbLabel feature-btns-label">Show Thumbnails</span></div><div class="captions feature-btns-control"><span class="captionLabel feature-btns-label">Show Captions</span></div></div><a class="slide-nav prev gallery-prev" rel="prev">Last Slide</a><a class="slide-nav next gallery-next" rel="next">Next Slide</a></div></div><p>At the New York premiere for "The Fault in Our Stars," producer Wyck Godfrey described to The Star the type of actress who will win the role of Margo.</p><p>"I want somebody that feels like that unattainable, awesome, cool girl in high school that a nerd like me couldn't get," Godfrey said. "I want to find somebody like that."</p><p>The Fox 2000 studio, producers Godfrey and Marty Bowen, screenwriters Scott Neustadter and Michael H. Weber, and actor Wolff are holdovers from the "The Fault in Our Stars" film.</p><div id="module-position-NiiE31bU36o" class="story-asset oembed-asset"><div class="oembed oembed-indystar oembed-type-link" data-oembed-type="link" data-oembed-provider="indystar"><style>
